<body>

    <nav class="navbar navbar-default navbar-fixed-top">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="navbar-header">
          <a class="navbar-brand" href="/"><strong>CodePair</strong></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="container">
          <div class="panel-group">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
              <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                  <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse1"><span class="fa fa-info"></span> What is Pair Programming?</a>
                </h4>
              </div>
              <div id="collapse1" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">Pair Programming is an agile software development technique in which two programmers work together at one workstation. The two programmers are classified as a Driver or Navigator.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div><br>
          <div class="panel-group">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
              <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                  <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseX"><span class="fa fa-info"></span> What is CodePair?</a>
                </h4>
              </div>
              <div id="collapseX" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">CodePair acts a virtual Workstation for Pair Programming. The two programmers can communicate through the chat bar. The Driver will create a session, and set who the navigator is by email, then link the session URL to the navigator, to begin the process. You must signup and be logged in to use CodePair! </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div><br>
          <div class="panel-group">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
              <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                  <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse2"><span class="fa fa-info"></span> What does the Driver do?</a>
                </h4>
              </div>
              <div id="collapse2" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">The Driver writes code. CodePair provides a Code Editor for the Driver to provide code for a Navigator. The Driver can upload code, download code or download chat messages.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div><br>
          <div class="panel-group">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
              <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                  <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse3"><span class="fa fa-info"></span> What does the Navigator do?</a>
                </h4>
              </div>
              <div id="collapse3" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">The Navigator provides feeback on the code provided by the Navigator. To collaborate the feedback, the Navigator can use the chat bar to convey were the code could be changed or improved. </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div><br>
    </div>

</body>
